      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Time for the 2YOs now where GOD'S HAMMER (5) makes plenty of appeal on the back of some handy trials coming in. He sat off the tempo in his latest heat and stormed over the top to score in an eye-catching effort. Maps for a similar run today with 1200m looking to suit. Happy to have him on top from ONE LAST RESORT (1) who bumped into a couple of smart ones in his debut campaign. His latest trial at Belmont under Azzopardi was solid and 1200m looks right up his alley. Wouldn't surprise to see him sit a touch closer and land the knockout blow. GOD'S ENCHANTMENT (4) looks to get plenty of favours on the map here on debut for the Stephen Miller barn. Brad Parnham sticks from his last two trials where he's shown enough to suggest he can make an impression. FROSTED WARRIOR (2) showed plenty of speed in his latest trial to win and 1200m first-up looks perfect. Big chance. DIVINE MIRAGE (7) is racing in good order and won't be far away.",
